      • build

        public ArrayData<X,Y> build()
        Builds ArrayData with given X and Y coordinates. If X coordinates are not specified, the method generates X coordinates as point indices i.e. the X coordinates go from 0 to Y.length - 1.
        Returns:
        constructed instance of ArrayData
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the Y coordinates are not provided
        IllegalArgumentException - if given coordinates have different lengths
